An Act relative to modernization of insurance laws.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Section 123 of said chapter 175, as so appearing, is hereby amended by striking out the
2 second paragraph and inserting in place thereof the following paragraph:
3 No life insurance company shall accept or take action on any request to change the
4 designation of beneficiary under any policy of life or endowment insurance unless the identity of
5 the person requesting the change is verified by the insurance company to the extent reasonable
6 and practicable. Verification may include a disinterested person witnessing the signature of the
7 person requesting the change, or other proof acceptable to the insurance company. For purposes
8 of this section, a disinterested person is one who is over eighteen years of age and not designated
9 as a beneficiary in the requested change. Upon receipt and acceptance of the change of
1 of 2

10 designation of beneficiary, the insurance company shall provide written notice of the change to
11 the policy owner at the owner's last known address.
